# Portfolio System - Architecture & Dependencies
## System Architecture
``` ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ FURNITURE VISUALIZER │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ ↓ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ NAVIGATION LAYER │ │ (Navigator.java - Member 1) │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Routes: │ │ - HOME → HomePanel │ │ - ROOM → RoomFormPanel (Member 2) │ │ - ROOMS → RoomTemplatesPage (Member 2) │ │ - FURNITURE → FurnitureLibraryPanel (Member 3) │ │ - EDITOR_2D → Editor2DPanel (Member 4) │ │ - VIEW_3D → View3DPanel (Member 5) │ │ - PORTFOLIO → PortfolioPanel ⭐ (YOUR TASK - Member 6) │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ ↓ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ APPLICATION STATE LAYER │ │ (DesignState.java - Member 1) │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ Singleton holding: │ │ - room: Room (current room being edited) │ │ - furnitureItems: List<FurnitureItem> (placed furniture) │ │ - listeners: notified when state changes │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ ↓ ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ DATA LAYER │ │ ⭐ YOUR RESPONSIBILITY ⭐ │ ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤ │ │ │ ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │ │ DesignModel.java │ │ │ │ ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │ │ │ │ Properties: │ │ │ │ - designId: UUID (unique per design) │ │ │ │ - userId: String (owner - multi-user) │ │ │ │ - designName: String (user-friendly name) │ │ │ │ - room: Room (the physical container) │ │ │ │ - furnitureItems: List<FurnitureItem> (contents) │ │ │ │ - createdAt, lastModifiedAt: LocalDateTime │ │ │ │ - tags, notes: String (metadata) │ │ │ │ - thumbnail: byte[] (preview image) │ │ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │ ↓ saves/loads │ │ ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │ │ DesignStorage.java │ │ │ │ ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │ │ │ │ CRUD Operations: │ │ │ │ - saveDesign(DesignModel): save new │ │ │ │ - updateDesign(DesignModel): modify existing │ │ │ │ - deleteDesign(designId): remove │ │ │ │ - getDesignsByUserId(userId): list user's designs │ │ │ │ - getDesignById(designId): load specific design │ │ │ │ - searchByName(userId, term): find designs │ │ │ │ - filterByTag(userId, tag): filter by tag │ │ │ │ │ │ │ │ Storage: Currently HashMap (in-memory) │ │ │ │ Future: MongoDB integration ready │ │ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │ ↑ displays │ │ ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │ │ │ PortfolioPanel.java ⭐ YOUR MAIN UI TASK ⭐ │ │ │ │ ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────── │ │ │ │ UI Components: │ │ │ │ - Grid layout (3 columns) │ │ │ │ - Design cards with: │ │ │ │ * Thumbnail image preview │ │ │ │ * Design name, room dimensions │ │ │ │ * Furniture count │ │ │ │ * Creation date │ │ │ │ - Action buttons per card: │ │ │ │ * ✏️ Edit (load for editing) │ │ │ │ * Export (download JSON/image) │ │ │ │ * ️ Delete (remove with confirmation) │ │ │ │ - Toolbar: │ │ │ │ * Search field (find by name) │ │ │ │ * Sort dropdown (date/name) │ │ │ │ * Refresh button │ │ │ │ - Info display: │ │ │ │ * Design count │ │ │ │ * Empty state message │ │ │ └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │ │ │ └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ ```
---
## Data Flow Diagrams
### Save Design Workflow
``` User in Editor2D ↓ Clicks " Save Design" button ↓ System prompts: "Enter design name" ↓ User types: "My Living Room" ↓ System collects: - DesignState.getRoom() → Room object - DesignState.getFurnitureItems() → List<FurnitureItem> - Session.getCurrentUser().getUserId() → String userId ↓ Creates DesignModel: new DesignModel( userId: "user-123", designName: "My Living Room", room: currentRoom, items: [sofa, table, lamp, ...] ) ↓ Saves to storage: DesignStorage.saveDesign(design) ↓ Storage adds to HashMap: designStore.put(designId, design) ↓ Shows success message ↓ User can view in Portfolio ```
### Load Portfolio Workflow
``` User clicks "Portfolio" button ↓ Navigator routes to PortfolioPanel ↓ PortfolioPanel initializes: - Gets userId: Session.getCurrentUser().getUserId() - Creates DesignStorage instance ↓ Loads user designs: DesignStorage.getDesignsByUserId(userId) ↓ Returns List<DesignModel> (filtered by userId) ↓ Sorts based on selected option: - "Date (Newest)" → sort by lastModifiedAt DESC - "Date (Oldest)" → sort by lastModifiedAt ASC - "Name (A-Z)" → sort by designName ASC - "Name (Z-A)" → sort by designName DESC ↓ Renders grid (3 columns): For each design: - Create JPanel card - Display thumbnail image - Show design info - Add action buttons ↓ Display count label ```
### Edit Design from Portfolio
``` User sees design in Portfolio ↓ Clicks "✏️ Edit" button ↓ System loads Design from storage: DesignStorage.getDesignById(designId) ↓ Populates DesignState: - DesignState.setRoom(design.getRoom()) - DesignState.clearFurnitureItems() - For each item: DesignState.addFurnitureItem(item) ↓ Routes to Editor2DPanel ↓ User sees room and furniture loaded ↓ Can continue editing (add/remove/move furniture) ↓ Clicks " Save Design" ↓ Saves updated design (same designId, updated timestamp) ```
### Delete Design Workflow
``` User sees design in Portfolio ↓ Clicks "️ Delete" button ↓ System shows confirmation dialog: "Delete 'My Living Room'?" ↓ User confirms ↓ System calls: DesignStorage.deleteDesign(designId) ↓ Storage removes from HashMap: designStore.remove(designId) ↓ Shows success message ↓ Refreshes portfolio grid (removes card) ```
---
## Class Dependency Map
``` ┌─────────────────────────────┐ │ PortfolioPanel.java │ │ (YOUR MAIN UI CLASS) │ └────────────┬────────────────┘ │ uses ↓ ┌─────────────────────┐ │ DesignStorage.java │ │ │ │ CRUD Operations: │ │ • saveDesign() │ │ • deleteDesign() │ │ • updateDesign() │ │ • getDesignsByUserId│ │ • searchByName() │ └────────┬────────────┘ │ manages ↓ ┌─────────────────────┐ │ DesignModel.java │ │ (Data Model) │ │ │ │ Properties: │ │ • designId │ │ • userId │ │ • designName │ │ • room │ │ • furnitureItems │ │ • createdAt │ │ • thumbnail │ └────────┬────────────┘ │ contains ┌───────┴────────┐ ↓ ↓ ┌──────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐ │ Room.java│ │ List<Furniture │ │ │ │ Item> │ │ • width │ │ • position (x,y)│ │ • length │ │ • rotation │ │ • shape │ │ • dimensions │ │ • color │ │ • type │ └──────────┘ └─────────────────┘
┌──────────────────────────┐ │ Session.java │ │ (Singleton - Auth) │ │ │ │ Provides: │ │ • getCurrentUser() │ │ • isLoggedIn() │ │ • logout() │ └───────────┬─────────────┘ │ used by ↓ ┌─────────────────┐ │ Navigator.java │ │ │ │ Manages: │ │ • PortfolioPanel│ │ • Editor2DPanel │ │ • Other panels │ └────────┬────────┘ │ uses ↓ ┌──────────────────┐ │ DesignState.java │ │ │ │ Holds: │ │ • current room │ │ • furniture list │ │ • listeners │ └──────────────────┘ ```
---
## Integration Points
### 1. With Navigator (UI Routing)
```java // In Navigator.java constructor this.portfolioPanel = new PortfolioPanel( () -> showHome(), // callback when back pressed this::loadDesignForEdit // callback when load pressed ); add(portfolioPanel, "PORTFOLIO");
// In button listener portfolioButton.addActionListener(e -> layout.show(this, "PORTFOLIO") // Switch to portfolio view ); ```
### 2. With Editor2DPanel (Save Designs)
```java // User saves current design // System gets data from DesignState Room room = designState.getRoom(); List<FurnitureItem> items = designState.getFurnitureItems();
// Creates and saves Design DesignModel design = new DesignModel(userId, name, room, items); storage.saveDesign(design); // Persisted!
// User can later load this design DesignModel loaded = storage.getDesignById(designId); designState.setRoom(loaded.getRoom()); designState.clearFurnitureItems(); loaded.getFurnitureItems().forEach(designState::addFurnitureItem); ```
### 3. With Session (Multi-user Support)
```java // Get current user ID for filtering String userId = Session.getInstance().getCurrentUser().getUserId();
// Load only user's own designs List<DesignModel> myDesigns = storage.getDesignsByUserId(userId);
// Save with user association design.setUserId(userId); storage.saveDesign(design); ```
### 4. With RoomRepository (Reference Pattern)
```java // RoomRepository pattern shows how to: // • CRUD operations // • HashMap storage // • Filtering // • Error handling // • Logging
// Copy this pattern for DesignStorage! // See: storage/RoomRepository.java (lines 1-100) ```
